# Architecture

Follow Clean Architecture with clear separation of concerns.

## Layering

- **Domain**: entities, value objects, business rules — no I/O or framework imports.
- **Application**: use cases and orchestration — depends on domain abstractions only.
- **Infrastructure**: provider implementations, persistence, HTTP clients — implements domain/application interfaces.
- **Interfaces**: CLI, API, or entry points — thin adapters that delegate to application layer.

## Dependency Rules

- Depend on abstractions (protocols/ABC), not concrete implementations.
- High-level modules must not import low-level modules; both depend on interfaces.
- Define interfaces in the domain or application layer; implement them in infrastructure.

## Design Principles

- **Interface-first**: define contracts before writing implementations.
- **Modularity**: one responsibility per module; avoid god objects and circular imports.
- **Extensibility**: prefer composition, registries, and plugin-style registration over conditionals.
- **Maintainability**: keep modules small; extract when a file mixes concerns.

## Repository Organization

```
src/<package>/
  domain/          # entities, interfaces, domain services
  application/     # use cases, orchestration
  infrastructure/  # provider implementations, adapters
  interfaces/      # CLI, API, entry points
tests/
  unit/
  integration/
docs/
```

- Keep domain and application free of provider-specific code.
- Colocate infrastructure adapters with their interface, not with business logic.
- Add new capabilities by extending interfaces and adding implementations — not by modifying core logic.
